<?xml  version='1.0' encoding='windows-1252' ?>
<xmi:XMI xmlns:xmi="http://schema.omg.org/spec/XMI/2.1" xmi:version="2.1" xmlns:uml="http://schema.omg.org/spec/UML/2.1" xmlns:thecustomprofile="http://www.sparxsystems.com/profiles/thecustomprofile/1.0">
	<xmi:Documentation exporter="Enterprise Architect" exporterVersion="6.5" exporterID="1714"/>
	<uml:Model xmi:type="uml:Model" name="EA_Model" visibility="public">
		<packagedElement xmi:type="uml:Package" xmi:id="EAPK_68F3A560_E3C8_422e_8A8A_D3464C8A967A" name="Emtiop" visibility="public">
			<ownedComment xmi:type="uml:Comment" xmi:id="EAID_3558F643_EEBA_4c41_A8E1_962241F8B26D" body="This subset of DC components should suffice to represent the DC side of an IBR converter."/>
			<ownedComment xmi:type="uml:Comment" xmi:id="EAID_70BE4C77_7C67_4da4_918F_11E741E8FAF5" body="This extension represents non-linear transformer core effects, through a piecewise-linear TransformerSaturation instance, which associates to linear TransformerCoreAdmittance and then to TransformerEnd."/>
			<ownedComment xmi:type="uml:Comment" xmi:id="EAID_8271D14C_510B_49d6_AC80_3C8C2898A131" body="These extensions eliminate Terminal objects from the IEEE P3743. Instead, ConductingEquipment and TransformerEnd extension instances associate directly to ConnectivityNode. Another extension represents non-linear transformer core effects, through a piecewise-linear TransformerSaturation instance, which associates to linear TransformerCoreAdmittance and then to TransformerEnd.">
				<annotatedElement xmi:idref="EAPK_68F3A560_E3C8_422e_8A8A_D3464C8A967A"/>
			</ownedComment>
			<ownedComment xmi:type="uml:Comment" xmi:id="EAID_0FB50C00_5BAC_4d9c_A43B_007185071E81" body="These classes define attributes and sets of Equipment associated with generating plants, large loads, etc.."/>
			<ownedComment xmi:type="uml:Comment" xmi:id="EAID_F285346A_4C68_4c70_8B10_EAF57553CC99" body="These classes associate a set of power flow ratings to a ConductingEquipment or TransformerEnd Terminal. The limit should be applied to the Terminal having sequenceNumber = 1. The direction should be absoluteValue. Voltage ratings are not included and no extensions are made."/>
			<ownedComment xmi:type="uml:Comment" xmi:id="EAID_118938DF_7E6A_4cdc_AC05_F82C84BFD8C5" body="These classes associate &quot;real-code&quot; dynamic link libraries (DLLs) to inverters and other Equipment, per Cigre TB 958. The IEEECigreDLLParameter does not need to inherit from DetailedModelDescriptor because it is already uniquely identified by the association to IEEECigreDLL in combination with its own sequenceNumber."/>
			<ownedComment xmi:type="uml:Comment" xmi:id="EAID_37686F36_5816_4b4e_957A_C860E89CFC65" body="These classes allow dynamic remote signal connections to ConnectivityNode, TransformerEnd, and either the From or To side of ConductingEquipment. It also permits the standard WeccDynamics and the extension IEEECigreDLL to use remote signals. &lt;font color=&quot;#ff0000&quot;&gt;What is the difference between remoteBusVoltage and remoteBusVoltageAmplitude?&lt;/font&gt;"/>
			<ownedComment xmi:type="uml:Comment" xmi:id="EAID_5567A377_5F25_4983_8492_59C5F34B7B45" body="The extension (top) associates SvVoltage to ConnectivityNode instead of TopologicalNode.&#xA;For ConductingEquipment, positive SvPowerFlow is defined from the Terminal into the equipment. This sign convention cannot be reversed. SvSwitch, SvStatus, SvTapStep, and SvShuntCompensatorSections are unchanged from the core CIM. SvInjection is not used.&#xA;Some inherited associations are hidden in this diagram for clarity. The phase attribute will not be used for describing positive sequence power flow results to initialize EMT. Instead, use the phase A reference angle in three-phase systems."/>
			<ownedComment xmi:type="uml:Comment" xmi:id="EAID_E7793D3B_7886_4ef5_81BB_0320EF6B493A" body="IEEECigreDLL inherits from DynamicsFunctionBlock."/>
			<packagedElement xmi:type="uml:Class" xmi:id="EAID_6774354F_3A1A_42c6_8771_7CE0A61015C8" visibility="public"/>
